						               													<description>Each player is a cat person looking to adopt stray cats until their house is full. Each of the cats comes with its own special ability, and sometimes they just go out for a walk without you knowing it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This revised version, Box of Cats 2022, offers a modified gameplay with additional cats and new abilities for greater fun!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;How to Play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Active player takes their turn with 3 phases.&amp;#10;1. Cat Phase, 2. Owner Phase and 3. Refill Phase&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1. Cat Phase: At the beginning of your turn, use the ability of each cat you have played into your House: from left to right.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. Owner Phase: Spend exactly 2 Action Points on the following actions. (You can choose the same action twice.)&amp;#10;- Cat in the House (1 Action Point): Choose 1 cat card from your hand and put it into play in front of you - from left to right. This area is your House.&amp;#10;- Stray Cats from the Box (1 Action Point): Choose 1 Stray Cat's Box (from the 3 available) and take all cards in that box into your hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can play any number of Action Cards during your turn. This counts as a free action.&amp;#10;Only Nope can be used in another player's turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3. Refill Phase: Fill each Stray Cat's Box with cards from the draw pile until each box has exactly 2 face-up cards.  The turn passes to the player on the left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;        note**&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- You can play any number of Action Cards during your turn. This counts as a free action.&amp;#10;Only Nope can be used in another player's turn.&amp;#10;- When Cats Walk is drawn, reveal it to every player and immediately use its ability. &amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;Each player chooses one cat in their House (not in their hand) and gives it to the player on their left - putting it into their House.&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;Game End &amp;amp; Scoring&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 2 ways to end the game.&amp;#10;1. When a player has five cats in their House, the player immediately wins the game.&amp;#10;2. When the 4th Cats Walk is revealed, the game ends without each player giving a cat to the player on their left. Total the cat scores and the player with the highest scores wins.&amp;#10;In case of a tie, the player with more cats in their House wins. If there is still a tie, the players share the victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
